The area

Address
Neighborhood: Graça & São Vicente
You can be thankful that most common travel guides don't mention Graça and São Vicente that often. Part of Lisbon's historic center and "Old Town", they feel like independent villages in the capital's center, and more untouched than Alfama. Amazing views, restaurants and parks, as well as important monuments like the S. Vicente Church and the National Pantheon, make this a spectacular option for those looking for a more tranquil walk-around in the center of Lisbon. Graça has been the choice of many younger people over the past years, both nationals and expats, given the cozy feeling of the neighborhood and its hidden secrets.
How to get there
  • Martim Moniz • 5 min walk
  • Rossio • 9 min walk

Stunning Views at Miradouro da Graça
Aug 2024 • Friends
Miradouro da Graça offers a beautiful view of the city, making it a perfect spot to unwind and soak in the scenery. We particularly enjoyed visiting during sunset; the golden light enhances the stunning landscape and creates a magical atmosphere.

Adding to the charm, there was music on the street, creating a lively ambiance that made our experience even more enjoyable. If you're in Lisbon, be sure to stop by this viewpoint for some breathtaking sights!

One of the better viewpoints in Lisbon with relatively easy access by trams
May 2023 • Couples
This is one of the better viewpoints in Lisbon. You can still see them, but Castelo de Sao Jorge is partly obscured by trees, and the 25 de Abril Bridge (Lisbon's Golden Gate Bridge) is barely peeking its head above the sea of tile roofs. To get here, take tram 28 and get off at the Graça / Miradouro da Graça stop. The viewpoint is about 100 meters (about 2-minute walk) away.
Written June 16, 2023

Hong Kong, China177,757 contributions
One of Lisbon's many rewarding viewpoints
Apr 2023
There are a handful of very good viewpoints (miradouros) scattered around Lisbon including this one just beside the Church of Our Lady of Grace in the Graca neighbourhood. From here there are really nice views of the west and if you look southwest you will have a very good view of St. George Castle as well.

There is a kiosk selling drinks and some tall pines at Miradouro da Graca, which is also called Miradouro Sophia de Mello Breyner Andresen (1919-2004), in memory of the Portuguese poet and writer who frequented this location during her lifetime.
Written June 11, 2023
